result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Antonio M. Givens

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: 4:15 p.m. Defendant Antonio M. Givens not in court.  Jillian Pfeifer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State moves to dismiss - Granted.

2:46 p.m. Defendant Antonio M. Givens in court.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Schiek states that DEJ has been reached - files agreement. State moves to dismiss Count 1 and domestic abuse enhancer on Count 2 - Granted. Defendant still wishes to proceed on own-Court questions defendant on previous waiver of counsel. Defendant enters no contest plea to Count 2 as amended.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and accepts the DEJ. Defendant questions regarding change of address and domestic abuse classes. Adj. 2:55 p.m.  Review hearing scheduled for December 12, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

1:26 p.m. Defendant Antonio M. Givens in court.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court questions defendant as to non-appearance. Defendant states he was in hospital with newborn son - thought hearing was at 1:00 - called courthouse between 10:30 and 11:00 and apologizes to Court for late appearance - Schiek states agreement has been offered - Defendant states he has accepted agreement  - Schiek states no agreement in file - Asst DA Bednar-Clemens file - Bail continued. Court quashes warrant previously authorized. Adj. 1:33 p.m.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 4, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Case called 11:45 a.m.:  Defendant Antonio M. Givens not in court.  Steven Mitchell Michlig appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Michlig statement to court - State notes in file that an offer has been extended to defendant - no other notes regarding adjournment.  Court notes that defendant did have proper notice of this appearance and was not advised by State not to appear.  Atty Michlig moves for warrant.  Court authorizes warrant.

1:18 p.m. Defendant Antonio M. Givens in court.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court questions defendant regarding non-appearance - Defendant states read paper wrong - thought appearance was on 27th - Court quashes warrant - Court questions defendant as to seeking counsel - Defendant states he will proceed on own - waiver free and voluntary - Court enters not guilty pleas Bednar statement - requests pre-trial date - Adj. 1:26 p.m.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 1, 2015 at 10:45 am.
2:54 p.m. Defendant Antonio M. Givens not in court.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court authorizes warrant. Adj. 2:55 p.m.
May not have abusive contact with Ashley Isham

1:25 p.m.   Defendant Antonio M. Givens in court, in custody, appears via video.  Steven Mitchell Michlig, Asst. DA, appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant in receipt of complaint, right to counsel - defendant will seek counsel. Michlig statement to bail - Court sets $1,500 signature bond.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 26, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
